#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn56.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.25:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Koṭigāmavagga "
msgstr "3. At the Village of Koṭi "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Āsavakkhayasutta "
msgstr "25. The Ending of Defilements "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn56.25:1.1"
msgid "“Jānatohaṃ, bhikkhave, passato āsavānaṃ khayaṃ vadāmi, no ajānato apassato. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I say that the ending of defilements is for one who knows and sees, not for one who does not know or see. "

msgctxt "sn56.25:1.2"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, jānato passato āsavānaṃ khayo hoti? "
msgstr "For one who knows and sees what? "

msgctxt "sn56.25:1.3"
msgid "‘Idaṃ dukkhan’ti, bhikkhave, jānato passato āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti jānato passato āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti jānato passato āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti jānato passato āsavānaṃ khayo hoti. "
msgstr "The ending of defilements is for one who knows and sees suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

msgctxt "sn56.25:1.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, jānato evaṃ passato āsavānaṃ khayo hoti. "
msgstr "The ending of the defilements is for one who knows and sees this. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn56.25:2.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.25:2.2"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
